    <div class="infobox-row"><div class="infobox-label">Title</div><div class="infobox-data">Embedded Intelligence Designer</div></div>
    <div class="infobox-row"><div class="infobox-label">Languages</div><div class="infobox-data">Italian, English, Spanish</div></div>
    <div class="infobox-row"><div class="infobox-label">Website</div><div class="infobox-data"><a href="https://guccione.work" target="_blank" rel="noopener">guccione.work</a></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- About -->
  <p>
    <b>Fabrizio Guccione</b> is an <a href="https://itp.nyu.edu">NYU ITP</a>-trained Embedded Intelligence Designer
    focused on AI-driven interactive systems and generative pipelines. His work bridges
    <a href="/projects">machine learning</a>, <a href="/projects">physical computing</a>, and
    <a href="/projects">fabrication</a> to create immersive experiences that exist in physical space rather than
    solely on screens.<sup class="wiki-ref">[1]</sup>
  </p>

  <p>
    Guccione currently serves as Fabrication Shop Staff at NYU ITP, where he trains over 300 students in
    <a href="/projects">laser cutting</a>, CNC milling, <a href="/projects">3D printing</a>, and machine embroidery
    across a 2,000-square-foot facility. He previously worked at <a href="https://www.mccann.com">McCann New York</a>
    exploring generative AI in advertising campaigns, and interned at <a href="https://adeam.com">ADEAM</a> constructing
    garments from sketch to runway.<sup class="wiki-ref">[2]</sup>
  </p>

  <p>
    His interests outside of work include playing guitar, cooking, and DJing.
  </p>

